    <section class="full history"> 
     <div class="col"> 
      <p>Los Angeles was little more than a frontier town in 1880 when USC first opened its doors to 53 students and 10 teachers in 1880, the “city” still lacked paved streets, electric lights, telephones and a reliable fire alarm system. Today, USC is home to more than 43,000 students and nearly 3,945 full-time faculty, and is located in the heart of one of the biggest metropolises in the world.</p> 
      <ul class="no-bullets"> 
       <li><a href="/history/">USC History</a></li> 
      </ul> 
     </div> 
     <div class="col"> 
      <h3 class="arrowhead">Timeline <span>Click the photos to learn more.</span> <mark></mark></h3> 
